10/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government approved a law Monday (9 June) granting amnesty to recruits who have avoided military service since 1992. 
Government spokesman Saso Colakovski explained that the law is part of government efforts to stimulate the integration of different segments of society. 
He said the law applies to 15,000 men who failed to join the army over the past 11 years.
In other news, Parliament Speaker Nikola Popovski says he wants to establish a police force to protect parliament. 
He says a special unit would improve the security of the national assembly, a common practice in other countries. 
(MIA, A1 TV - 09/06/03)
